<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-n8q0heM9JwjrF2fZUOqEsQ" name="mng_safe_rel_reqs,_k-ggoL0kEd-ja4kCHc-Zyw" guid="-n8q0heM9JwjrF2fZUOqEsQ" changeDate="2010-10-25T16:12:13.468-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>The hazard analysis is a key document that captures hazards, risks, faults, and control measures together. The control&#xD;
measures mitigate the risks and so must be captured as requirements on the system to manage the risks to an acceptable&#xD;
level.</mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_VN51gOCNEd-aE9U0mRj03A" name="Study hazard analysis" guid="_VN51gOCNEd-aE9U0mRj03A">
    <sectionDescription>The hazard analysis summaries the hazards, faults, risks, and safety/reliability measures.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_ZqEe0OCNEd-aE9U0mRj03A" name="Identify hazards" guid="_ZqEe0OCNEd-aE9U0mRj03A">
    <sectionDescription>Hazards are conditions to avoid. Hazards are analyzed using Fault Tree Analysis and/or Failure Means and Effect Analysis.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_auBPIOCNEd-aE9U0mRj03A" name="Quantify risks" guid="_auBPIOCNEd-aE9U0mRj03A">
    <sectionDescription>Risk is the product of the severity of a hazard and its likelihood.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_bwxsoOCNEd-aE9U0mRj03A" name="Identify safety and relaibility measures" guid="_bwxsoOCNEd-aE9U0mRj03A">
    <sectionDescription>Safety/reliability measures are design or analysis elements that decrease risk by either obviating the hazard, reducing its&#xD;
likelihood or reducing its severity.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_d3VJcOCNEd-aE9U0mRj03A" name="Update hazard analysis" guid="_d3VJcOCNEd-aE9U0mRj03A">
    <sectionDescription>This step updates the hazard analysis with results of the safety and reliability analysis.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>The purpose of this task is to identify and clarify the safety and reliability issues of the system for the purpose of&#xD;
identifying relevant safety and reliability requirements.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
